05/12/2006
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The new Republika Srpska Council of Peoples (CoP) held its constituent session on Monday (December 4th).
The mandates of the 28 deputies, elected after the October 1st general vote in BiH, were verified.
Bosniak Dzevad Osmancevic was named CoP speaker.
The panel acts like an upper house of the Bosnian Serb entity parliament.
The Croat, Bosniak and Serb communities have eight representatives each, while smaller communities have four.
(RTRS, Srna - 04/12/06)
